#!/usr/bin/env bash
# SPDX-License-Identifier: Apache-2.0
#
# SessionStart hook: warns when the Claude Code session is operating in the
# shared `default` jj workspace. Stays silent in any additional workspace or
# when the repo is not jj.
#
# Why: jj snapshots the working copy on EVERY jj command. When you edit in the
# shared default workspace, any other jj command boundary in the same
# workspace — including those run by dispatched subagents (which fetch + `jj
# new`) or by hooks — can move `@` off your in-flight change. If that change
# is unnamed, it is effectively orphaned. Isolating into a per-task workspace
# removes the collision surface.
#
# Detection: in the main checkout (default workspace) `.jj/repo` is a
# DIRECTORY; in an additional workspace it is a FILE (a pointer back to the
# main `.jj`). Ported from holomush's scripts/jj-main-repo.sh.
#
# Output contract: SessionStart hooks concatenate stdout into the session's
# additional context. Emit the warning to stdout; stay silent (exit 0, no
# output) when no warning is needed. This hook is purely informational and
# MUST NEVER block session start.

set -euo pipefail

# Consume the JSON event from stdin (no field needed; honor the contract).
cat >/dev/null 2>&1 || true

# Resolve the current workspace root. If jj is unavailable or this is not a
# jj repo, stay silent — the hook is a no-op outside jj.
ws_root="$(jj workspace root 2>/dev/null || true)"
[ -n "$ws_root" ] || exit 0

if [ -d "$ws_root/.jj/repo" ]; then
  : # default workspace — fall through to warn
elif [ -f "$ws_root/.jj/repo" ]; then
  exit 0 # additional workspace — already isolated, stay silent
else
  exit 0 # not resolvable as a jj workspace — stay silent
fi

cat <<'EOF'
**You are in the shared `default` jj workspace.** jj snapshots the working copy on every `jj` command, so a dispatched subagent or hook running a `jj` command in this same workspace can move `@` off your in-flight change and orphan it (this is how uncommitted/unbookmarked work gets lost here). Before editing files for a task, isolate this session:

- **Agents / Claude Code:** use the `EnterWorktree` tool (it triggers the dev-flow plugin's `WorktreeCreate` hook → a sibling jj workspace under `<repo>_worktrees/<name>`, trunk-based + bookmarked, registered with the harness so the working directory persists).
- **Manual fallback:** `jj workspace add ../<repo>_worktrees/<name> --name <name>` then `cd` in and `jj bookmark create <name> -r @`.
- See the `dev-flow:using-worktrees` and `jj:jujutsu` skills for the full pattern.

If you are only reading/answering (no file edits), you can ignore this warning.
EOF
